parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The distortion and expansion of the fuel tank can cause the tank to leak fuel, leading to a potential fire hazard, and can also impede steering and handling, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The fuel tank expands and distorts
causing it to no longer fit properly on the frame
the handlebars hit the tank on turning
and the tank presses against the ignition switch. The tank latch may become inoperable
and the rubber mounts may no longer sit on the frame.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The swelling and blistering of the gas tank can cause fuel leakage, electrical issues, and potentially lead to a fire hazard, which can result in serious injury or accident.
symptoms: Swelling or bulging of the gas tank
blistering or bubbling at the base of the tank where it meets the seat
electrical issues or malfunction of the ignition switch.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the ignition switch can cause electrical issues, stalling, or failure to start the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: potential fuel leakage due to gas tank swelling.
